extendedInfo.description: Sync your Android device with your Mac. This special Android module of SyncMate will help you sync your Android device with a Mac via Wi-Fi, USB or Bluetooth. You can synchronize contacts, calendars, folders, Safari bookmarks, iTunes and iPhoto; mount your Android as a new volume on a Mac, manage your text messages (SMS) conveniently and more. Check it out!SyncMate for Android is just a sync client app!ï£¿ï£¿ï£¿ The main sync software should be installed on your Mac ï£¿ï£¿ï£¿Go to http://www.sync-mac.com/downloads/ for additional download.

reviews.title: More trouble than it is worth.. Best avoided
reviews.comment: After a recent update the app deleted all my future calendar events.  Support have not responded to my request for help.  It creates duplicate contacts in the address book.  Support is either non-existent or very slow.  I bought the \'Expert\' version, then an update came out, I tried the update which offered no advantages, so wanted to return to previous version, but was told that I could not return to the previous version and would have to pay again to get the \'Expert\' version.
reviews.author: Michael Lank

reviews.title: SyncMate
reviews.comment: Note sure what people\'s issues are. works well for me. not sure why people don\'t read too. I clearly understood only contact and calendar syncing were the free plug ins. I suggest ignoring all negative reviews based on the \"it\'s not free\" factor. I too had a positive experience with support. I suppose of you\'re on a jerk, they\'ll help. fair enough right? no issues with macbook <-> RAZR hd and htc one. Some crashes on desktop app but overall good. I\'ve recommended.
reviews.author: Juan Gonz\303\241lez

reviews.title: Terrible App - One of the Worst
reviews.comment: It\'s one thing to have an app that doesn\'t work very well, or crashes, or is hard to use.  It\'s a whole other thing when it trashes important existing data on your smartphone and computer.   This app has basically made my existing calendaring function and data completely unusable.  There is massive amounts of duplication that happens when you sync calendars - it does not recognize existing info.  In some cases I now have 8 instances of the same appointment.  You have to go through your entire calendar and delete all dups manually every time it syncs.  Then for reoccurring appointments - it gets it wrong - putting them on the wrong days, weeks or months.  Are you kidding?  They are actually trying to sell this stuff - it\'s the worst app I\'ve ever used.   After reading the other reviews - I see that this is a low quality product put out by folks who obviously don\'t know what they are doing and don\'t care what damage they are causing to their users.  Otherwise they would have fixed this - and it\'s not that complicated to fix.  I\'ve been a software engineer for 35 years - and know that this is due to bad software design and coding - and could be fixable.  But they have not.
reviews.author: Brian Price

reviews.title: Didn\'t work.  Terrible service.
reviews.comment: I downloaded this app and was never able to sync photo albums even after following all instructions and purchasing the very expensive sync mate expert license.  I sent all of the program logs requested by their support team and was never provided with a solution.  When I requested a refund I was told that I must have a team viewer session with their support team (after I told them I am not available during business hours which is the only time they can have a session).  App never worked,  terrible service.
reviews.author: Andrea Petersen

reviews.title: It is free, don\'t expect much!!!
reviews.comment: I installed this application after I uninstalled Missing Sync because I couldn\'t get it to work with my iMac. I can say that Syncmate was ridiculously easy to install in both my Samsung Galaxy S3 and my iMac. It syncs calendar and contacts well. However it would be great if it let us sync music, pictures and videos without having to pay $40. I think it is too expensive.

reviews.comment: I was able to sync my contacts from a macbook to a LG phone not supported by isync from Apple.
reviews.author: Marta Diana

reviews.title: BEWARE!!!!!!!
reviews.comment: The app and solution is pretty ok. However, as a web developer since 1998, I\'ve interacted with hundreds (thousands?) various support and helpdesks. Some excellent, some fair, some bad and some really, really bad. But Eltimas \"support\" beats them all. Their \"support\" simply doesn\'t exist.   So, roll the dice. Either buy their app and hope you\'ll never have any problems. Or get a slightly less fancy gadget like e.g. AirDroid or The Missing Sync for Android (free) and never worry at all.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Very good. The best I have found so far.
reviews.comment: Ok, I tried many sync tools to try and sync my Galaxy S3 with my Mac Book Pro and this beats them all hands down. It works, it is very comprehensive in what it does. I can sync music, photo\'s, video and more between the two devices quickly and seamlessly. It evens allows you to mount your Android device as a disk without issue.... and all over Wifi. I do have one issue with syncing iPhoto events, I have raised this with support which I hope they can resolve. All in all though, I recommend this, very good indeed.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Paranoid Developer
reviews.comment: It synchronizes my iCal and Contacts from my Mac to the Galaxy Note 2. It works more or less, but makes often errors about deleted entries and other things. But the worst on this software is, the desktop client demands contact to Eltimas registering server all 7 days. So if you can not connect to the web or Eltima decides not to support SyncMate anymore or Eltima gets shut down, you can not start your desktop client anymore. Money completely wasted. This is about the most paranoid developer I have ever seen. And this for a third-class little helper app, its ridiculous. It is so customer unfriendly that I can only recommend: hands off! Also: It does not update detail informations, for example if you add a phone number to an existing contact on the Mac, the change does not get synced to the mobile.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Not sure what peoples problems are?
reviews.comment: I have just installed SyncMate on my Macbook Pro (MacBookPro5.5) and connected to my Galaxy S3 via USB with zero effort. Plugged in, turned on USB with debugging as advised in the application and connected. Took 2-3 minutes.   I enquired about an issue with external SD cards and mounting them and had a proper helpful e-mail response in about 15 minutes actually answering my question and resolving it. So clearly Customer Service is working.   SyncMate is so much better than the standard Android Mac file transfer which is basically rubbish.   Its made pretty clear that this is a paid for application, why do people think it should be free? Grow up, read the web site and try it out.   I don\'t need it to sync calendars or contacts as I have separate applications that link into my corporate mail and calendars.   The new version they sent me handles internal and external SD cards correctly. I use that to move music around as I actually don\'t want to auto sync given I have 100GB of music.  I use this on two Mac\'s as per the license and had the same easy experience.  So overall I find it works well, is easy to install, the customer service has been good for me.
reviews.author: Rob Willett

reviews.title: App is fine, but the $40 expert edition is bull.
reviews.comment: Got this to try and sync tunes and movies to my Nexus 7, realized that I would need to spend about $40 to download the \"expert\" version to do anything worthwhile with Syncmate on my Mac. Insta-delete, and Insta-1 star. Disclose your REAL fees before you do stuff like that.   AVOID THIS APP!
reviews.author: Ian Sassa

reviews.title: Don\'t buy product!
reviews.comment: No customer support! I purchased the expert edition (v3) for $40 a few months ago this year. I had a problem with my computer and asked for them to send me a copy of v3. They\'re telling me that now they have version 4 and no longer support v3 and I have to pay an additional $40 to get the expert edition! WTF! Additionally, it will cost extra for CD copies, lifetime upgrades, etc... Now I\'m stuck with a fully paid product with limited use!
reviews.author: A Google User
